@node "REQUIREMENTS" "Requirements"
@next "INSTALLATION"
@prev "IMPORTANT"

 =========================================================================
                     	    REQUIREMENTS
 =========================================================================


	This little script is an example of the AREXX multi-process 
	communication capability. MessPlus needs Varexx and Dignet,
	(both included).
	
	MUIMess+ needs MUIRexx and Dignet.

	You would need a computer with:

		- MC68000 or better

		- Kickstart version 37 or later

		- Arexx (RexxMast)
                
		- A device that is serial.device compatible (or the
		  serial.device itself of course)

		- US Robotics Message Plus Modem (Check Flash memory
		  update on www.3com.com)
 
		- External speaker or headphones.
		
		- MUIRexx (see dev/mui on Aminet mirrors)
	
        You can modify the used device in line 16.

	Developed on an A1230 Tower/50 Mhz with 18 MB ram.

        
 =========================================================================
@endnode

@node "INSTALLATION" "INSTALLATION"
@next "USAGE"
@prev "REQUIREMENTS"

 =========================================================================
             		 INSTALLATION GUIDE
 =========================================================================



	This little script is written in AREXX and use VAREXX or MUIRexx
	to handle its GUI and DIGNET to dialog with the serial port. 

	Varexx and Dignet are included in this archive, you won't 
	need to download them from Aminet. If you prefer the MUI GUI, 
	you MUST download and install MUIRexx and icon.mcc (included in
	MUIRexx archive) before installing MessPlus.
	Then, all you have to do is : 
	
	- Connect an external speaker or headphones at dedicated modem's
	  back connector. Unfortunately, USR disabled the possibility
	  to play on phone line in SM+ mode :-(.
	
	- Unpack this archive somewhere
	
	- Click on the install icon, and follow the script... 
	
 	To launch messplus you can click on its icon from Workbench or type
 	in a shell : rx mess+ or rx MUIMessPlus

	For INTERNET Users : 
	
	You can set automatically your modem in the right mode using these
	2 scripts :
	
	- MESS+_Inactive.rexx can be launch from Miami as "Start" event.
 	
 	- MESS+_Active.rexx can be launch from Miami as "End" event.

  	If you want to start Mess+ every warm up, you can place its icon in 
	your WBStartup directory.

	That's all folks !!


	Read about the @{"usage" link "USAGE" 0}.

                                              
 =========================================================================
@endnode

@node "USAGE" "Usage guide"
@next "CONFIG"
@prev "INSTALLATION"

 =========================================================================
                    	 USAGE GUIDE
 =========================================================================


	This GUI is as intuitive as possible, but you can't guess essential
	stuff to use your modem correctly. These advices are given in the
	@{"IMPORTANT NOTES" link "IMPORTANT" 0} part of this guide.
  
	This proggy is kindof  a "modem's GUI". Most of your actions are
	simply send to the modem, wich excecute them. For basic actions 
	the modem works for about 1 sec. It's much longer for complex actions
	like storing messages... The pointer is busy every time your modem
	is working...

	You MUST @{"record" link "CONFIG" 0} the "Greeting" and "Memory full" messages. Also
	don't forget to SAVE your settings in modem memory once you set them
	all, otherwise the modem won't keep them.


	@{"CONFIGURATION Options" link "CONFIG" 0}.
	@{"MEMORY Options" link "MEMORY" 0}.
	@{"About modem's LEDs" link "LEDS" 0}.
	@{"Distant Verification" link "DISTANT" 0}.

 	For guidelines or modem's answers, look at STATUS gadget. 

	Message Plus internal software isn't done to keep messages "ad vitam 
	eternam", so delete them as soon as you checked them. You also should
	switch your modem OFF time to time to cool it a little.

	Every startup takes about 15 sec : getting current's modem configu-
	ration, messages informations, setting up in right mode and error
	handling. If Messplus get weird modem answers and can't be initialized 
	it correctly, you'll been asked to switch it OFF/ON.

 =========================================================================
@endnode

@node "CONFIG" "CONFIGURATION Options"
@next "MEMORY"
@prev "USAGE"

 =========================================================================
                       CONFIGURATION Options
 =========================================================================


        Active                  - Switch On/Off the stand alone answering
        			  mode.

        Voice			- Switch On/Off the possibility to store
				  or handle incoming Voice calls.
        			  
        Fax			- Switch On/Off the possibility to store
				  or handle incoming Faxs.

        Remote			- Allow remote message consultation. You
				  must enter your desired 4 digits pass-
        			  word in the next gadget.

        Reset Clock		- Reset modem's internal clock and save
      				  current time in #4 phone number memory.

	GREETING/Mem FULL	- Select wich one you want to record or
				  play.

        REC.			- Record the selected message. Wait for
				  tones before speaking (directly to the
				  modem at 50 cm). These messages can be
				  up to 15 sec. long. Always click STOP 
				  to store your message.

	PLAY			- Plays current configuration message.

	STOP			- ALWAYS click here after recording. Be
				  patient, the store process is long.

	SAVE			- Save all settings in non volatile RAM.


 =========================================================================
@endnode

@node "MEMORY" "MEMORY Options"
@next "LEDS"
@prev "CONFIG"

 =========================================================================
                       MEMORY Options
 =========================================================================


	% FULL 			- Indicates percentage of memory used.

	VOICE			- Number of voice messages stored.

	FAX 			- Number of Fax stored.

	PLAY			- Play current selected voice message.

	ERASE ALL		- Erase all stored messages.


 =========================================================================
@endnode

@node "LEDS" "Modem's LED"
@next "DISTANT"
@prev "MEMORY"

 =========================================================================
                     About Modem's LEDs
 =========================================================================



	The ARQ/FAX or "SM+" LED is used to indicate Modem's functionality.
	A dual color LED is used. Uses as regular Voice/Fax modem, LED will 
	be red and the functionality described in the User's Manual will 
	occur. 
	
	The Message Plus stand alone answering mode needs to enables the
	modem's "Self-mode", the LED will be green. 
	
	The LED will be solid green, if there are no unreleased messages 
	present in the SM+ Memory. 
	
	The SM+ LED will blink once slowly for each new message. 
	
	The SM+ LED will blink fast if the SM+ Memory is full. The state 
	of the SM+ LED always reflects the current state of the SM+ Memory
	when the Self-mode is enabled.


 =========================================================================
@endnode


@node "DISTANT" "Modem's LED"
@next "ENHANCE"
@prev "LEDS"

 =========================================================================
                     DISTANT CHECKING
 =========================================================================


   Explanations from USR :
   -----------------------

	Once a DTMF digit is detected during call selection, the Dialup
	Password verification is started. The user has three chances to 
	enter the correct password. 
	
	If he fails to enter the correct password, the call is aborted 
	and the modem goes back on hook. 
	
	If the correct password is entered, the modem acoustically indicates 
	the number of present messages (new) including the case of no new 
	messages.
	
	The user may then enter the DTMF digit 0 to repeat the acoustic 
	indication of new messages count. The DTMF digit 1 will start 
	playback of all Unchecked Messages. The DTMF digit 2 will start 
	playback of all Stored Messages. 
	
	While playing back messages, the DTMF digit 1 restarts the playback
	of currently played voice message. The DTMF digit 2 aborts current 
	playback, marks the aborted message as checked, and start playing
	the next selected message. 
	
	When there are no more voice messages selected for playback, the 
	modem acoustically indicates the end of currently played message 
	and waits for more DTMF tones for a predefined amount of time. The
	user can either hang up the SM+ Modem by DTMF digit * or the modem
	hangs up automatically after a certain period of time has expired.


 =========================================================================
@endnode


@node "ENHANCE" "Enhancements"
